        "weight": "PRIMARY",
        "note": "All four rings active. Ring 1 dominates — corpus overwhelmingly concerns inner cognitive and dispositional life. Ring 2 substantially present: God remembers, commands remembering, renews the nous (Rom 12:2), writes law on dianoia (Heb 8:10), gives mind of Christ (1Cor 2:16). Ring 3 present through shared-mind vocabulary, remembrance in prayer, conscience in community. Ring 4 marginal through noēma (Satan's designs, 2Cor 2:11, 4:4)."
      },
      "spirit_soul_body": {
        "weight": "SECONDARY",
        "note": "Mind operates primarily at soul-level (seat of intentions, thoughts, memory). Spirit-level engagement explicit in 1Cor 14:14-15 (nous vs pneuma in prayer). Body appears as instrument and marker of mind-states. Somatic-attention connection implicit throughout sha.mar corpus."
      },
      "inner_operations": {
        "weight": "PRIMARY",
        "note": "Full range documented: remembering and forgetting, planning and devising, inclining and orienting, evaluating from within (conscience), changing (metanoeō, na.cham), collapsing into madness or maintaining sobriety, attending deliberately. Renewal of the mind (Rom 12:2) is the most distinctive inner operation — divine action transforming the mind's fundamental orientation."
      },
      "being": {
        "weight": "PRIMARY",
        "note": "Ye.tser (formed inclination) documents the dispositional substrate of inner life. Sōfrōn family documents formed character of sound-mindedness. Froneō in Phil 2:5 operates as permanent characterising disposition. Mind of Christ (1Cor 2:16) is the supreme example of transferred orientation of being — not a moment of insight but a transferred character."
      }
